DUBAI: Dubai-based actress Lindsay Lohan is set to partner with Netflix on two new features, the US star revealed on her Instagram. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle Details about the new productions are yet to be announced, but in a statement Netflix’s head of independent productions, Christina Rogers, said: “We’re so happy with our collaboration with Lindsay to date, and we’re thrilled to continue our partnership with her.” A post shared by Lindsay Lohan (@lindsaylohan) The new deal confirms Lohan’s complete return to acting after years of on-and-off parts, and she is also planning her wedding to Dubai-based financier fiance Bader Shammas. In addition to the new works, Lohan has also signed with Netflix to star in a holiday rom-com film “Falling for Christmas” that is set for release later this year.